==Spanish==
===Etymology===
"Little jump", [[diminutive]] of ''[[salto]]'' "a jump", from Latin ''[[saltus]]'', from ''[[salio|salire]]'' "to jump", from Proto-Indo-European ''*sal-yo-''. Related to English ''[[sally]]''.
===Noun===

# Saltillo.